Dear Mr New NonTeam Professional,
One of your patients, Mrs Emis Patient 1, wants to share their medical records with you using the Patients Know Best secure online service. Mrs Patient 1 was legally verified by EMIS Org name.

To start helping your patient, you need to register free of charge using the following link:

http://pkb-frontend-13/clinicianRegistrationUserForm.action?invitationId=e7f72370-622f-4321-8968-da4544cca1cf&invitationKey=oexdTJJ9GVC9zfjQ&e=indepedent.professional%40pro.test

Message from Mrs Emis Patient 1

Just do it...

Questions?

  1. Is this medically secure? Patients Know Best is HIPAA-compliant for US patients and Data Protection Act compliant for European ones. The site is part of the UK NHS secure network (N3), so it is already built to NHS security standards and approved for usage with any NHS computer.
  2. Do I have to register with the web site? Yes, but registration is free and fast. Please click here: http://pkb-frontend-13/clinicianRegistrationUserForm.action?invitationId=e7f72370-622f-4321-8968-da4544cca1cf&invitationKey=oexdTJJ9GVC9zfjQ&e=indepedent.professional%40pro.test
  3. What happens after I register? Your patient will send you messages when they need you to look at their records, and you can see their discussions with other professionals at other institutions. You can also send messages and add to the patient's records.
Please do not reply to this email; this address is not monitored. Click this link to log into your record.

Yours,

Patients Know Best Help Team
